3EA%20new%20report%20has%20shed%20light%20on%20the%20status%20of%20state%20finances%2C%20highlighting%20the%20persistent%20budget%20revenue%20deficit.%20This%2C%20according%20to%20the%20report%2C%20is%20leading%20to%20limitations%20on%20capital%20outlay%2C%20specifically%20the%20allocation%20of%20funds%20to%20create%20assets.%20%3Cstrong%3E%3Cbr%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20also%20points%20out%20that%20the%20goods%20and%20services%20tax%20(GST)%20slabs%20need%20to%20be%20rationalised%20for%20the%20post-compensation%20period.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Union%20government%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fnews%2Fnational%2Ftamil-nadu%2Fpalanivel-thiaga-rajan-hits-out-at-centre-on-non-extension-of-gst-compensation-period-levy-of-cess%2Farticle66642173.ece%5C%22%3Ehad%20refused%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20extend%20the%20original%20GST%20compensation%20period%2C%20which%20affected%20the%20states%E2%80%99%20revenues.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20GST%20was%20introduced%20on%20July%201%2C%202017%2C%20and%20June%2030%2C%202022%20marked%20the%20end%20of%20the%20transition%20period%20during%20which%20the%20states%20were%20compensated%20for%20any%20loss%20in%20revenue%20due%20to%20the%20implementation%20of%20the%20new%20tax%20regime.%20This%20was%20calculated%20as%20the%20difference%20between%20the%20projected%20revenue%20based%20on%20a%2014%25%20annual%20growth%20with%202015-16%20as%20the%20base%20year%20and%20the%20actual%20GST%20revenue.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20also%20says%20that%20electricity%20subsidies%20form%20about%20half%20of%20total%20expenditure%20by%20states.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20titled%20%E2%80%98State%20of%20State%20Finances%E2%80%99%20was%20released%20by%20PRS%20Legislative%20Research%2C%20a%20non-profit%20independent%20research%20institute%2C%20on%20October%201%20(Wednesday).%20It%20has%20been%20authored%20by%20Tushar%20Chakrabarty%20and%20Tanvi%20Vipra.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EStates%20continue%20to%20budget%20revenue%20deficit%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EA%20revenue%20deficit%20implies%20that%20the%20revenue%20generated%20by%20a%20state%20is%20not%20enough%20to%20cover%20its%20estimated%20revenue%20expenditure%20which%20includes%20salaries%2C%20pensions%2C%20etc.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20other%20words%2C%20this%20means%20that%20the%20state%20governments%20are%20consistently%20spending%20more%20money%20than%20they%20are%20generating%20through%20their%20regular%20sources%20of%20income%2C%20such%20as%20taxes%2C%20fees%2C%20and%20other%20revenue%20streams.%20Their%20expenses%20exceed%20their%20income.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThis%20puts%20a%20limitation%20on%20the%20creation%20of%20assets.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20noted%20that%20since%202015-16%2C%20seven%20states%20have%20persistently%20reported%20a%20revenue%20deficit.%20These%20states%20are%20Andhra%20Pradesh%2C%20Haryana%2C%20Kerala%2C%20Punjab%2C%20Rajasthan%2C%20Tamil%20Nadu%2C%20and%20West%20Bengal.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAll%20recent%20Finance%20Commissions%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feconomictimes.indiatimes.com%2Fnews%2Feconomy%2Fpolicy%2Ffinance-ministry-releases-revenue-deficit-grant-of-rs-7183-42-cr-to-14-states%2Farticleshow%2F95354291.cms%5C%22%3Ehave%20recommended%20grants%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20states%20to%20eliminate%20revenue%20deficits.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%2015th%20Finance%20Commission%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fopinion%2Feditorial%2Fnavigating-the-storm-the-hindu-editorial-on-the-fifteenth-finance-commission%2Farticle33897255.ece%5C%22%3Ehas%20recommended%3C%2Fa%3E%20revenue%20deficit%20grants%20of%20nearly%20Rs%202.95%20lakh%20crore%20for%2017%20states%20over%20the%20next%20five%20years%2C%20from%202021-22%20to%202025-26.%20Around%2087%25%20of%20the%20grants%20were%20awarded%20in%20the%20first%20three%20years%2C%20the%20report%20said.%20Therefore%2C%20the%20grants%20in%20the%20next%20two%20years%20will%20be%20substantially%20lower%2C%20and%20states%20will%20have%20to%20augment%20their%20revenue%20sources%20or%20cut%20expenditures%20to%20maintain%20revenue%20balance.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EKerala%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fcity%2Fthiruvananthapuram%2Fkerala-gets-largest-share-of-revenue-deficit-grant%2Farticleshow%2F95847583.cms%5C%22%3Ereceived%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20largest%20share%20of%20the%20revenue%20deficit%20grant%20of%20Rs%204%2C749%20crore.%20It%20won%E2%80%99t%20receive%20any%20grants%20in%202023-24.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20added%20that%2011%20states%20have%20budgeted%20a%20revenue%20deficit.%20Out%20of%20these%2011%20states%2C%20Andhra%20Pradesh%2C%20Himachal%20Pradesh%2C%20Kerala%2C%20Punjab%2C%20and%20West%20Bengal%20have%20budgeted%20revenue%20deficit%20after%20accounting%20for%20revenue%20deficit%20grants%20in%202023-24.%20If%20grants%20were%20not%20provided%2C%20six%20more%20states%2C%20including%20Assam%2C%20Nagaland%2C%20and%20Uttarakhand%2C%20would%20have%20been%20in%20revenue%20deficit%20in%202023-24.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ENote%20that%20states%E2%80%99%20own%20tax%20revenue%20is%20the%20largest%20source%20of%20revenue%20for%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%202023-24%2C%20states%20on%20aggregate%20are%20estimated%20to%20have%20raised%2057%25%20of%20their%20revenue%20receipts%20from%20their%20own%20tax%20and%20non-tax%20sources%2C%20while%2043%25%20is%20estimated%20to%20have%20come%20from%20the%20devolution%20of%20central%20taxes%20and%20grants%20from%20the%20Union%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%202023-24%2C%20states%E2%80%99%20revenue%20expenditure%20is%20budgeted%20to%20be%2083%25%20of%20their%20total%20expenditure%20while%20capital%20outlay%20is%20budgeted%20to%20be%2017%25%2C%20the%20report%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2Funion-government-tax-devolution-rhetoric-crisis%5C%22%3EBehind%20Union%20Govt%E2%80%99s%20Rhetoric%20of%20Higher%20Tax%20Devolution%20for%20States%20Lies%20a%20Silent%20Fiscal%20Crisis%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ERationalise%20GST%20slabs%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EStates%E2%80%99%20GST%20revenue%20has%20been%20consistently%20lower%20than%20the%20guaranteed%20revenue.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThis%20is%20because%20states%E2%80%99%20aggregate%20GSDP%20has%20grown%20at%20a%20compounded%20rate%20of%209.6%25%20between%202018-19%20and%202022-23%2C%20lower%20than%20the%2014%25%20guaranteed%20growth%20rate%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20report%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhen%20the%20GST%20was%20introduced%20in%20July%202017%2C%20states%20were%20given%20a%20revenue%20guarantee%20of%2014%25%20per%20annum%20on%20their%20GST%20revenue%20over%20the%20base%20year%202015%E2%80%9316.%20However%2C%20not%20many%20states%20had%20a%20growth%20rate%20of%20subsumed%20taxes%20higher%20than%2014%25%20pre-GST%2C%20with%20most%20of%20them%20falling%20in%20the%205%25%E2%80%9312%25%20growth%20rate%20band%2C%20the%20%3Cem%3EEconomic%20and%20Political%20Weekly%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.epw.in%2Fjournal%2F2020%2F47%2Fcommentary%2F14-revenue-guarantee-states-justified.html%5C%22%3Ereported%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20December%202020.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EStates%20that%20fell%20short%20of%20this%20annual%20GST%20revenue%20growth%20were%20compensated%20until%20the%20end%20of%20June%202022.%20The%20compensation%20to%20the%20states%20was%20being%20met%20through%20the%20levy%20of%20a%20GST%20compensation%20cess%20on%20specified%20goods%20and%20services.%20However%2C%20the%20end%20of%20the%20compensation%20affected%20their%20revenues.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EMoreover%2C%20the%2015th%20Finance%20Commission%20had%20observed%20that%20the%20GST%E2%80%99s%20revenue%20neutrality%20was%20compromised%20due%20to%20multiple%20tax%20rate%20reductions.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%20lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20GST%20Council%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fbusiness%2Findia-business%2Ffinance-ministry-starts-process-for-deciding-on-convenor-of-gst-rate-rationalisation-gom%2Farticleshow%2F100911391.cms%3Ffrom%3Dmdr%5C%22%3Ehad%20in%20September%202021%20decided%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20set%20up%20a%20Group%20of%20Ministers%20(GoM)%20for%20r%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fspan%3Eationalising%20tax%20exemptions%20and%20correcting%20the%20inverted%20duty%20structure%20(where%20the%20tax%20on%20finished%20or%20processed%20goods%20is%20lower%20than%20the%20tax%20on%20the%20raw%20materials%20or%20intermediate%20products%20used%20to%20manufacture%20those%20finished%20goods).%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20its%2047th%20meeting%2C%20the%20GST%20Council%20had%20recommended%20several%20tax%20rate%20changes%20to%20reduce%20exemptions%20and%20correct%20the%20inverted%20duty%20structure.%20However%2C%20the%20changes%20have%20not%20been%20adopted%20so%20far%2C%20says%20the%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAfter%20five%20months%2C%20the%2048th%20GST%20Council%20meeting%2C%20held%20on%20December%2017%2C%20was%20a%20%E2%80%9Cdisappointing%20affair%E2%80%9D%2C%20because%20there%20was%20no%20correction%20of%20the%20inverted%20duty%20structure%2C%20an%20exercise%20which%20also%20led%20to%20the%20rationalisation%20of%20rates%2C%20Najib%20Shah%2C%20former%20chairman%20of%20the%20Central%20Board%20of%20Indirect%20Taxes%20%26amp%3B%20Customs%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cnbctv18.com%2Fviews%2Fview--the-48th-gst-council-meeting-was-a-disappointing-affair-15503531.htm%5C%22%3Ewrote%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20CNBC-TV18.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThere%20was%20no%20attempt%20either%20to%20move%20towards%20the%20much-debated%20convergence%20of%20rates%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20PRS%20report%20also%20highlighted%20that%20%E2%80%9Cat%20present%2C%20SGST%20accounts%20for%20over%2040%25%20of%20states%E2%80%99%20own%20tax%20revenue.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAnd%2C%20therefore%2C%20GST%20slabs%20may%20need%20to%20be%20rationalised%20to%20get%20additional%20revenue%20in%20the%20post-compensation%20period%2C%20it%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Findia-states-welfare-spending-debt%5C%22%3EHow%20Indian%20States%20Can%20Prioritise%20Welfare%20Spending%20While%20Tackling%20High%20Debts%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EInflating%20subsidy%20expenditure%3Cbr%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%202022-23%2C%20states%20are%20estimated%20to%20spend%209%25%20of%20their%20revenue%20on%20subsidies.%20These%20include%20electricity%20supply%2C%20health%2C%20education%2C%20and%20transportation.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EA%20major%20portion%20of%20the%20states%E2%80%99%20expenditure%20goes%20towards%20providing%20subsidised%20electricity%20for%20agriculture%2C%20domestic%20and%20industrial%20use%2C%20the%20report%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIn%202021-22%2C%20a%20large%20share%20of%20the%20subsidy%20expenditure%20went%20towards%20providing%20subsidised%20electricity.%20Notably%2C%2097%25%20of%20Rajasthan%20and%2080%25%20of%20Punjab%20and%20Bihar%E2%80%99s%20total%20subsidy%20expenditure%20went%20towards%20subsiding%20electricity%20in%202021-22%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20International%20Monetary%20Fund%20(IMF)%20has%20noted%20that%20a%20substantial%20portion%20of%20the%20benefits%20from%20these%20subsidies%20may%20primarily%20reach%20higher-income%20households.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EPRS%20conducted%20a%20case%20study%20on%20Punjab%E2%80%99s%20subsidy%20expenditure.%20It%20said%20that%20the%20subsidy%20expenditure%20as%20a%20share%20of%20revenue%20receipts%20has%20been%20significantly%20high%20in%20the%20state.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBetween%202017-18%20and%202021-22%2C%20Punjab%20spent%2017%25%20of%20its%20revenue%20receipts%20on%20subsidies.%20Other%20states%2C%20on%20average%2C%20spent%208%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1699018191000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F03172102%2FH20230218126655.jpg