Farticleshow%2F104946856.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Hamas%20wants%20to%20wreck%20years%20of%20US%20efforts%20to%20mend%20Israel-Arab%20ties%20%E2%80%94%20and%20it%20looks%20like%20it's%20working%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22US-Saudi%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6544ceb6b788914e554f75c4%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22512%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EUS%20Secretary%20of%20State%20Antony%20Blinken%20(L)%20meets%20with%20Saudi%20Foreign%20Minister%20Prince%20Faisal%20bin%20Farhan%20in%20Riyadh%20on%20October%2014%2C%202023.%3Cp%3EJACQUELYN%20MARTIN%2FPOOL%2FAFP%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%20%3Cli%3EHamas'%20attacks%20on%20Israel%20on%20October%207%20aimed%20at%20derailing%20Saudi-Israel%20talks%2C%20analysts%20say.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3EIsrael's%20attacks%20on%20Gaza%20have%20sparked%20fury%20in%20the%20region%2C%20imperiling%20years%20of%20diplomacy.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3EBut%20Saudi%20and%20UAE%20leaders%20say%20they%20remain%20committed%20to%20normalizing%20ties.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20early%20October%2C%20President%20Joe%20Biden%20seemed%20poised%20to%20achieve%20a%20historic%20prize%3A%20normalizing%20relations%20between%20Israel%20and%20Saudi%20Arabia%2C%20the%20most%20powerful%20country%20in%20the%20Middle%20East.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20discussions%20were%20part%20of%20a%20process%20which%20began%20in%202020%20under%20President%20Donald%20Trump%2C%20when%20Bahrain%20and%20the%20United%20Arab%20Emirates%20began%20formal%20diplomatic%20relations%20with%20Israel%2C%20bringing%20economic%20and%20military%20benefits.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20process%20went%20so%20smoothly%20because%20it%20ignored%20the%20hardest%20issue%20to%20resolve%3A%20what%20to%20do%20about%20the%20Palestinian%20territories.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20October%207%2C%20ignoring%20that%20suddenly%20became%20impossible%20%E2%80%94%20which%20was%20likely%20just%20what%20Hamas%20intended.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIts%20militants%20rampaged%20through%20southern%20Israel%2C%20killing%201%2C400%20Israelis%2C%20kidnapping%20and%20torturing%20others.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIsrael's%20retaliatory%20attacks%20on%20Gaza%20killed%20thousands%20more%2C%20badly%20straining%20its%20delicate%20relations%20with%20its%20Arab%20neighbors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EProtesters%20in%20Bahrain%2C%20Egypt%2C%20and%20Morocco%20are%20demanding%20that%20their%20leaders%20punish%20Israel%2C%20and%20reverse%20the%20diplomatic%20gains%20of%20recent%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20Thursday%20Bahrain%2C%20one%20of%20the%20original%20signatories%20of%20the%20Trump-era%20Abraham%20Accords%2C%20said%20it%20would%20recall%20its%20ambassador%20to%20Israel.%20It%20was%20a%20stark%20sign%20of%20its%20leaders'%20concern%20over%20the%20carnage%20in%20Gaza%2C%20and%20mounting%20public%20fury.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E(A%20spokesperson%20for%20the%20Israeli%20government%20told%20Insider%20that%20it%20had%20yet%20to%20be%20directly%20informed%20of%20any%20recall.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIsraeli%20war%20crimes%20in%20Gaza%20and%20worsening%20violence%20and%20oppression%20in%20the%20West%20Bank%20are%20fueling%20a%20tremendous%20amount%20of%20rage%20in%20the%20wider%20Arab-Islamic%20world%2C%26quot%3B%20Giorgio%20Cafiero%2C%20the%20CEO%20of%20Gulf%20State%20Analytics%2C%20told%20Insider.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20leaders%20in%20the%20region%20remain%20shaken%20by%20the%20Arab%20Spring%20which%20felled%20several%20Middle%20Eastern%20governments%20a%20decade%20ago%20%E2%80%94%20and%20fear%20what%20a%20new%20popular%20uprising%20could%20do%20to%20their%20own%20grip%20on%20power.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAny%20government%20in%20the%20Arab%20world%20that%20considers%20joining%20the%20Abraham%20Accords%20would%20face%20high%20levels%20of%20risk%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20potential%20backlash%20from%20domes