2C%20got%20a%20law%20degree%2C%20and%20landed%20plum%20clerkships.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ENow%20a%20judicial%20committee%20has%20determined%20that%20there%20will%20be%20no%20official%20investigation.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20federal%20courts%20have%20spiked%20an%20investigation%20into%20racist%20text%20messages%20sent%20by%20a%20conservative%20activist-turned-law%20clerk%20who%20got%20jobs%20working%20alongside%20two%20federal%20judges%20with%20the%20full-throated%20support%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fclarence-thomas-supreme-court-is-not-worth-doing-for-pay-2023-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EClarence%20Thomas%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202015%20and%202016%2C%20Crystal%20Clanton%20was%20a%20key%20leader%20at%20Turning%20Point%20USA%2C%20Charlie%20Kirk's%20youth-oriented%20conservative%20nonprofit.%20She%20got%20a%20picture%20with%20Donald%20Trump's%20sons%2C%20mobilized%20high-school%20activists%2C%20and%20trashed%20liberal%20academics%20in%20an%20appearance%20on%20Fox%20News.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20all%20came%20crashing%20down%20when%20the%20New%20Yorker%20reported%20in%202017%20that%20she%20had%20texted%20a%20friend%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20HATE%20BLACK%20PEOPLE.%20Like%20fuck%20them%20all.%26quot%3B%20The%20existence%20of%20the%20texts%2C%20sent%20when%20she%20was%20in%20college%2C%20was%20confirmed%20by%20the%20Washington%20Post%20in%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20source%20also%20shared%20a%20screenshot%20of%20the%20texts%20with%20Insider%20on%20the%20condition%20it%20not%20be%20published.%20Her%20offensive%20messages%20are%20followed%20by%20quotidian%20chit-chat%20about%20meeting%20at%20Starbucks%2C%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.washingtonpost.com%2Fopinions%2F2022%2F01%2F18%2Fclerk-texts-appeals-court-clanton%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ethe%20Post%20reported%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20her%20exile%2C%20Clanton%20attended%20law%20school%20and%20even%20lived%20for%20a%20time%20with%20Clarence%20and%20Ginni%20Thomas.%20She%20also%20landed%20clerkships%20with%20two%20federal%20judges%20%E2%80%94%20Judge%20Corey%20Maze%2C%20a%20federal%20district%20judge%20in%20Alabama%2C%20and%20Judge%20William%20Pryor%2C%20an%20influential%20appellate%20judge.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELast%20year%2C%20a%20federal%20judicial%20panel%20ordered%20that%20an%20investigation%20take%20place%20into%20whether%20Clanton%20actually%20sent%20the%20texts.%20But%20according%20to%20an%20October%2031%20decision%2C%20Pryor%20and%20Maze%20successfully%20argued%20that%20the%20panel%20didn't%20have%20the%20authority%20to%20order%20an%20investigation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20in%20today's%20zero-sum%20political%20environment%2C%20Clanton's%20elevation%20comes%20as%20a%20shock%20to%20some.%20William%20Hodes%2C%20a%20legal%20ethics%20guru%20who%20once%20represented%20a%20white%20supremacist%20who%20was%20fighting%20to%20become%20a%20licensed%20lawyer%2C%20said%20in%20an%20email%20exchange%20with%20Insider%20last%20year%20that%20judges%20should%20know%20better%20than%20to%20hire%20someone%20like%20Clanton.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEven%20pre-law%20school%20behavior%20like%20this%20should%20disqualify%20one%20from%20a%20federal%20clerkship%20%E2%80%94%20not%20as%20a%20legal%20matter%20but%20because%20the%20judges%20should%20have%20the%20sensibility%20to%20look%20elsewhere%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3EOther%20judges%20took%20Clarence%20Thomas's%20word%20that%20Crystal%20Clanton%20isn't%20racist%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20bombing%20out%20of%20Turning%20Point%2C%20Clanton%20has%20won%20praise%20from%20some%20of%20her%20law-school%20peers%20and%20professors%20%E2%80%94%20along%20with%20one%20of%20the%20most%20influential%20judges%20in%20America.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMediaite%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mediaite.com%2Fonline%2Fexclusive-clarence-thomas-wife-hired-ex-tpusa-staffer-known-for-saying-i-hate-blacks%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ereported%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%202018%20that%20Clanton%20got%20a%20job%20helping%20Ginni%20Thomas%20with%20media%20production.%20She%20enrolled%20in%20and%20graduated%20from%20George%20Mason%20University's%20Antonin%20Scalia%20Law%20School%2C%20and%20Clarence%20Thomas%20later%20said%20that%20she%20lived%20with%20him%20and%20Ginni%20for%20about%20a%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Atlanta%20Journal-Constitution%20wrote%20that%20Thomas%20himself%20had%20vouched%20for%20Clanton.%20%26quot%3BI%20know%20Crystal%20Clanton%20and%20I%20know%20bigotry%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.abajournal.com%2Fnews%2Farticle%2Ffederal-judges-who-hired-law-clerk-accused-of-racist-statements-wont-face-misconduct-complaints%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ereportedly%20wrote%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%26quot%3BBigotry%20is%20antithetical%20to%20her%20nature.%26quot%3B%20He%20also%20claimed%2C%20without%20evidence%2C%20that%20she%20was%20a%20victim%20of%20%26quot%3Bdefamation.%26quot%3B%20(Clanton%20herself%20has%20never%20claimed%20that.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EClanton%20didn't%20respond%20to%20phone%20calls%20or%20a%20text%20sent%20to%20a%20number%20listed%20for%20her%20in%20a%202022%20bar%20record.%20The%20Supreme%20Court%20public%20information%20officer%20also%20didn't%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment%20directed%20to%20Thomas%2C%20and%20Pryor%20didn't%20respond%20to%20an%20email%20sent%20to%20him%20by%20Insider%20through%20a%20court%20press%20officer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20closest%20Clanton%20has%20come%20to%20apologizing%20or%20acknowledging%20the%20texts%20was%20in%20the%20New%20Yorker%20article.%20%26quot%3BI%20have%20no%20recollection%20of%20these%20messages%20and%20they%20do%20not%20reflect%20what%20I%20believe%20or%20who%20I%20am%20and%20the%20same%20was%20true%20when%20I%20was%20a%20teenager%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20told%20writer%20Jane%20Mayer.%20(She%20was%2020%20when%20she%20sent%20the%20texts.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20finishing%20law%20school%2C%20Clanton%20clerked%20for%20Maze%2C%20a%20federal%20judge%20in%20Anniston%2C%20Alabama%20from%202022%20to%202023.%20She%20got%20that%20job%20because%20she%20was%20recommended%20for%20it%20by%20Judge%20Pryor%2C%20who%20hadn't%20yet%20worked%20with%20Clanton%2C%20according%20to%20a%20person%20with%20knowledge%20of%20her%20hiring.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESuch%20placements%20aren't%20unusual%20in%20the%20world%20of%20federal-court%20clerkships.%20Pryor%20is%20the%20chief%20judge%20of%20the%20Eleventh%20Circuit%20Court%20of%20Appeals%2C%20and%20his%20word%20carries%20a%20lot%20of%20sway%20with%20other%20judges.%20He%20is%20one%20of%20a%20handful%20of%20judges%20nationwide%20with%20a%20reputation%20as%20a%20%26quot%3Bfeeder%20judge%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20one%20whose%20clerks%20often%20go%20on%20to%20clerk%20with%20Supreme%20Court%20justices.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20news%20of%20Clanton's%20jobs%20with%20Maze%20and%20Pryor%20sparked%20outcry.%20Media%20outlets%20and%20members%20of%20Congress%20assailed%20her%20hiring.%20The%20official%20response%20was%20bare-bones.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20case%20was%20referred%20to%20the%20Second%20Circuit%2C%20an%20appeals%20court%20based%20in%20New%20York.%20Judge%20Debra%20Livington%2C%20the%20Second%20Circuit's%20chief%20judge%2C%20wrote%20in%202022%20that%20Judges%20Pryor%20and%20Maze%20simply%20concluded%20that%20the%20New%20Yorker's%20reporting%20wasn't%20true.%20The%20decision%20to%20hire%20her%20was%20based%20on%20the%20recommendations%20she'd%20gotten%2C%20including%20from%20Charlie%20Kirk%2C%20who%20had%20sent%20her%20packing%20in%202017.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3EA%20thorough%20investigation%20ordered%20and%20then%20canceled%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20another%20obscure%20panel%20of%20judges%20%E2%80%94%20the%20Committee%20on%20Judicial%20Conduct%20and%20Disability%20of%20the%20Judicial%20Conference%20of%20the%20US%20%E2%80%94%20essentially%20reversed%20course.%20They%20said%20Maze%20and%20Pryor's%20diligence%20wasn't%20good%20enough%20and%20called%20for%20an%20investigation%20that%20would%20entail%20contacting%20the%20people%20named%20in%20the%20New%20Yorker%20article%20as%20having%20knowledge%20of%20Clanton's%20actions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20was%20in%20July%202022.%20In%20its%20new%20decision%2C%20the%20Second%20Circuit%20panel%20revealed%20that%20Maze%20and%20Pryor%20objected%2C%20saying%20that%20the%20Judicial%20Conduct%20and%20Disability%20panel%20had%20no%20authority%20to%20order%20an%20investigation.%20So%20the%20Second%20Circuit%20panel%20consulted%20with%20the%20Judicial%20Conference's%20Executive%20Committee%2C%20a%20group%20of%20seven%20judges%2C%20which%20concluded%20this%20past%20June%20that%20Maze%20and%20Pryor%20were%20right.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGabby%20Fe%2C%20one%20of%20the%20people%20named%20in%20the%20New%20Yorker%20story%20making%20claims%20of%20racism%20against%20Clanton%2C%20called%20the%20decision%20%26quot%3Boutrageous.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHodes%2C%20the%20legal%20ethicist%2C%20said%20that%20even%20judges%20who%20think%20the%20New%20Yorker%20or%20its%20reporter%20Jane%20Mayer%20have%20an%20ax%20to%20grind%20against%20Clarence%20Thomas%20should%20want%20the%20facts%20to%20be%20uncovered.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20way%20too%20much%20here%20for%20the%20%5BSecond%20Circuit%5D%20to%20have%20just%20dismissed%20it%20as%20'insufficiently%20proven'%20or%20'sufficiently%20investigated%2C'%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20Insider%20in%20his%20email.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3EDo%20you%20know%20more%3F%20Insider%20would%20like%20to%20speak%20with%20you.%20Call%20or%20send%20a%20Signal%20message%20to%20reporter%20Jack%20Newsham%20at%20314-971-1627%20using%20your%20personal%20phone.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcrystal-clanton-racist-texts-clarence-thomas-investigation-dropped-2023-11%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A169