.8%25%2C%20the%20unemployment%20rate%20rose%20slightly%20to%203.9%25.%20That's%20just%20above%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.investing.com%2Feconomic-calendar%2Funemployment-rate-300%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eforecast%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%203.8%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22raw%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FWAvbf%2F10%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22US%20unemployment%20rate%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22450%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EWage%20growth%20slowed.%20Average%20hourly%20earnings%20increased%20by%200.2%25%20from%20September%20to%20October%2C%20following%20month-over-month%20increases%20of%200.3%25.%20Average%20hourly%20earnings%20increased%20by%204.1%25%20from%20October%20last%20year%20to%20October%20this%20year%2C%20following%20year-over-year%20increases%20of%20around%204.3%25%20in%20recent%20months.%20These%20earnings%20stood%20at%20%2434.00%20in%20October.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20labor%20force%20participation%20rate%20was%2062.7%25%20in%20October%2C%20similar%20to%20the%2062.8%25%20seen%20previously.%20The%20employment-population%20ratio%20was%2060.2%25%2C%20just%20below%20the%2060.4%25%20seen%20during%20the%20past%20few%20months.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECompared%20to%20other%20major%20industries%20that%20saw%20a%20one-month%20employment%20decline%20in%20October%2C%20manufacturing%20saw%20the%20largest%20drop.%20Employment%20in%20this%20industry%20fell%20by%2035%2C000.%20Employment%20in%20motor%20vehicles%20and%20parts%20saw%20a%20drop%20of%20around%2033%2C000%2C%20which%20can%20partly%20be%20attributed%20to%20strike%20activity%20per%20the%20news%20release%20from%20BLS.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20of%20the%20industries%20that%20saw%20job%20growth%20from%20September%20to%20October%20included%20healthcare%2C%20construction%2C%20and%20leisure%20and%20hospitality.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22no