ole%20as%20the%20second-largest%20contributor%20to%20UN%20peacekeeping%20operations%2C%20a%20position%20it%20holds%20despite%20being%20kept%20off%20the%20command%20responsibilities%20it%20deserves.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBut%20there%20were%20two%20issues%20besides%20world%20peace%20that%20Guterres%20clearly%20wanted%20to%20highlight%3A%20the%20transforming%20world%20climate%2C%20and%20Nepal%20as%20a%20path-breaker%20in%20the%20arena%20of%20transitional%20justice.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20separate%20helicopter%20trips%20to%20the%20base%20of%20Mount%20Everest%20and%20the%20Annapurna%20Sanctuary%2C%20the%20secretary-general%20relied%20on%20the%20experience%20of%20the%20mountain%20people%20to%20sound%20the%20alarm%20on%20the%20climate%20crisis%2C%20three%20weeks%20before%20COP%2028%20is%20to%20start%20in%20Dubai.%20The%20highly%20populated%20%E2%80%98third%20pole%E2%80%99%20of%20the%20planet%20indeed%20serves%20as%20a%20barometer%20of%20global%20warming%2C%20and%20the%20receding%20glaciers%20of%20an%20inhabited%20Himalaya%20are%20a%20more%20potent%20bellwether%20of%20climate%20catastrophe%20than%20the%20Arctic%20or%20Antarctica.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EJoint%20session%20of%20parliament%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EFor%20Nepal%2C%20the%20most%20significant%20aspect%20of%20the%20Secretary-General%E2%80%99s%20visit%20was%20the%20suspended%20transitional%20justice%20(TJ)%20process%2C%20which%20began%20with%20the%20end%20of%20the%20decade-long%20Maoist%20insurgency%20in%202006.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20matter%20languishes%20even%20though%20the%20Maoist%20rebels%20have%20long%20since%20joined%20mainstream%20politics%20and%20the%20commandant%20of%20the%20Maoist%20force%20is%20presently%20the%20prime%20minister.%20He%20is%20in%20that%20position%20despite%20holding%20no%20more%20than%2011%25%20of%20seats%20in%20parliament%2C%20but%20that%20is%20another%20story.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EPrime%20Minister%20Pushpa%20Kamal%20Dahal%20(nom%20de%20guerre%3A%20%E2%80%98Prachanda%E2%80%99)%20had%20hoped%20to%20use%20the%20secretary-general%E2%80%99s%20trip%20to%20show%20off%20his%20international%20standing%20to%20the%20Nepali%20populace%2C%20and%20to%20get%20a%20green%20signal%20from%20the%20secretary-general%20for%20his%20tendentious%20plans%20to%20push%20a%20perpetrator-friendly%20TJ%20draft%20law%20through%20Parliament.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EDespite%20an%20overwhelming%20show%20of%20obsequiousness%20from%20Dahal%20who%20followed%20him%20at%20practically%20every%20step%20around%20the%20country%2C%20the%20secretary-general%20did%20not%20oblige%20his%20host.%20Instead%2C%20Guterres%20used%20every%20pulpit%20during%20his%20trip%20to%20insist%20that%20Nepal%E2%80%99s%20TJ%20process%20be%20concluded%20within%20three%20parameters%3A%20a)%20concurrence%20of%20the%20victims%20of%20conflict%3B%20b)%20concordance%20with%20relevant%20international%20law%20and%20principles%3B%20and%2C%20c)%20following%20the%20precedence-setting%20judgements%20on%20transitional%20justice%20by%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20of%20Nepal.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20victims%20of%20Nepal%E2%80%99s%20conflict%20did%20not%20get%20to%20meet%20the%20secretary-general%2C%20as%20requested%2C%20their%20various%20submissions%20were%20put%20together%20in%20a%20file%20and%20presented%20to%20Guterres%20as%20he%20departed%20for%20the%20airport%20on%20the%20morning%20of%20November%201%20by%20Hanaa%20Singer-Hamdy%2C%20the%20UN%20Resident%20Coordinator%20to%20Nepal.%20She%20said%20in%20her%20comment%20on%20X%20(Twitter)%3A%20%E2%80%9CThe%20needs%20and%20priorities%20of%20the%20conflict%20victims%20are%20at%20the%20heart%20of%20Transitional%20Justice-related%20discussion%20in%20Nepal.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F03153718%2FF90eJxcbQAAIHll.jpeg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F03153718%2FF90eJxcbQAAIHll.jpeg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F03153718%2FF90eJxcbQAAIHll-300x196.jpeg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F03153718%2FF90eJxcbQAAIHll-1024x670.jpeg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-683363%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22785%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EHanaa%20Singer-Hamdy%20hands%20over%20the%20memorandum%20submitted%20by%20various%20conflict%20victims%20organisations%20to%20Antonio%20Guterres.%20Photo%3A%20X%2F%40SingerHanaa%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EMaking%20of%20An%20Exemplary%20Process%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20secretary-general%20clearly%20understands%20that%2C%20worldwide%2C%20the%20fraught%20arena%20of%20transitional%20justice%20has%20had%20too%20few%20successes%2C%20whereas%20it%20provides%20the%20pathway%20for%20post-conflict%20societies%20to%20heal%20and%20recover%20%E2%80%93%20through%20reparation%2C%20memorialisation%2C%20truth%20and%20reconciliation%2C%20not%20to%20forget%20accountability%20for%20extreme%20cases%20of%20human%20rights%20abuse.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHerein%20lies%20the%20importance%20of%20Nepal%2C%20where%20the%20Nepali-led%20transitional%20justice%20process%20is%20presently%20stuck%2C%20but%20the%20victims%20and%20rights%20defenders%20have%20not%20let%20go.%20The%20international%20community%2C%20and%20especially%20the%20United%20Nations%2C%20can%20help%20by%20ensuring%20that%20there%20is%20principled%20monitoring.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThat%20the%20Nepali%20players%20are%20capable%20of%20moving%20the%20boat%20to%20the%20other%20shore%20was%20what%20Guterres%20emphasised%20in%20his%20address%20on%20October%2031%20to%20a%20joint%20session%20of%20Parliament.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ENepal%E2%80%99s%20transitional%20justice%20process%20could%20become%20an%20example%20for%20post-conflict%20societies%20the%20way%20Colombia%2C%20South%20Africa%20and%20Sierra%20Leone%20are%20today%20held%20out%20for%20their%20relative%20success.%20Within%20South%20Asia%2C%20a%20region%20awash%20in%20long-term%20conflict%20from%20Kashmir%20to%20Sri%20Lanka%2C%20Afghanistan%20and%20Balochistan%20to%20the%20Arakan%2C%20transitional%20justice%20is%20not%20%E2%80%98deployed%E2%80%99%20anywhere%20else%20other%20than%20in%20Nepal.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAll%20the%20more%20reason%20for%20the%20Nepali%20process%20to%20succeed%20in%20order%20to%20provide%20a%20model%20for%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20region%20to%20consider%2C%20and%20for%20Guterres%20to%20dwell%20on%20the%20matter%20during%20his%20visit.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIronically%2C%20the%20main%20roadblock%20to%20a%20proper%20conclusion%20of%20the%20peace%20process%20was%20the%20secretary-general%E2%80%99s%20host%2C%20the%20prime%20minister.%20While%20Dahal%20used%20the%20conflict%20and%20the%20ensuing%20peace%20process%20to%20build%20his%20personal%20political%20career%2C%20he%20understands%20that%20a%20genuine%20transitional%20justice%20exercise%20would%20jeopardise%20his%20trajectory%20and%20pre-eminent%20position%20in%20Nepali%20politics.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20entire%20superstructure%20of%20his%20Maoist%20party%20would%20collapse%20were%20he%20to%20submit%20his%20colleagues%20to%20an%20accountability%20process%2C%20even%20if%20only%20%E2%80%98emblematic%20cases%E2%80%99%20were%20to%20be%20investigated.%20Hence%2C%20the%20formula%20used%20on%20the%20TJ%20over%20a%20decade%20and%20more%20has%20been%20prevarication%20and%20duplicity.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20government%20security%20personnel%20who%20would%20have%20been%20involved%20in%20atrocities%20during%20the%20conflict%20of%201995-2006%20are%20all%20retired%20by%20now%2C%20whereas%20the%20Maoist%20leadership%20is%20today%20part%20of%20Nepal%E2%80%99s%20political%20establishment%2C%20ruling%20the%20roost.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThey%20are%20loathe%20to%20be%20held%20accountable%2C%20which%20is%20why%20their%20supremo%20Dahal%20cannot%20countenance%20an%20honest%20exercise%2C%20and%20which%20is%20why%20he%20was%20hoping%20to%20bamboozle%20Guterres%20with%20pomp%20and%20flattery.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EVictims%20and%20spoilers%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhile%20there%20has%20historically%20been%20ferocious%20bloodletting%20in%20the%20Kathmandu%20court%20among%20clans%20and%20factions%20vying%20for%20power%2C%20and%20also%20during%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%98unification%20exercise%E2%80%99%2C%20the%20villages%20of%20Nepal%20have%20been%20largely%20free%20of%20internecine%20violence%20until%20the%20decade%20of%20insurgency%20and%20state%20response.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20villagers%20of%20Nepal%20were%20caught%20in%20a%20pincer%20between%20the%20Maoist%20rebels%20who%20specialised%20in%20hit-and-run%20raids%20and%20the%20security%20forces%20that%20meted%20out%20harsh%20treatment%20to%20local-level%20political%20leaders%2C%20teachers%20and%20development%20workers.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EDahal%E2%80%99s%20role%20may%20be%20held%20up%20for%20scrutiny%20in%20a%20genuine%20Truth%20and%20Reconciliation%20process%2C%20for%20he%20headed%20the%20chain%20of%20command%20of%20the%20Maoist%20insurgents.%20His%20attitude%20to%20atrocities%20including%20murder%2C%20torture%2C%20rape%20and%20abduction%20conducted%20by%20his%20cadre%20has%20always%20been%20ambiguous%2C%20and%20there%20has%20been%20no%20expression%20of%20remorse%20throughout%20his%20years%20in%20open%20politics.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIf%20anything%2C%20there%20has%20been%20gleeful%20celebration%20of%20extra-judicial%20killing%20and%20physical%20violence%20generally%2C%20and%20he%20has%20even%20expressed%20satisfaction%20with%20how%20he%20personally%20fooled%20the%20United%20Nations%20Mission%20in%20Nepal%20(UNMIN)%20into%20tripling%20the%20number%20of%20Maoist%20combatants%20in%20a%20verification%20exercise.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%202007%2C%20upon%20coming%20above%20ground%2C%20Dahal%20told%20a%20BBC%20interlocutor%20that%20in%20a%20personal%20circular%20during%20the%20conflict%2C%20he%20had%20instructed%20that%20%E2%80%9Cyou%20may%20eliminate%20individuals%20if%20required%2C%20but%20without%20torture%E2%80%9D.%20Over%20the%20years%2C%20Dahal%20has%20been%20the%20key%20leader%20who%20ensured%20that%20successive%20Truth%20and%20Reconciliation%20Commissions%20were%20designed%20for%20failure%2C%20with%20their%20membership%20padded%20with%20Maoists.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EMost%20recently%2C%20Dahal%E2%80%99s%20attempt%20has%20been%20to%20push%20through%20legislation%20that%20would%20make%20it%20easy%20for%20the%20next%20Truth%20and%20Reconciliation%20Commission%20to%20let%20perpetrators%20(of%20both%20sides%2C%20rebels%20and%20state%20security)%20off%20the%20hook%20by%2C%20among%20other%20things%2C%20creating%20two%20categories%20of%20murder%3A%20%E2%80%98normal%20murder%E2%80%99%20and%20%E2%80%98extreme%20murder%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhat%20makes%20the%20secretary-general%E2%80%99s%20interest%20in%20Nepal%E2%80%99s%20transitional%20justice%20efforts%20vitally%20important%20is%20that%20the%20Western%20governments%20and%20INGOs%20who%20introduced%20the%20concept%20and%20funded%20Nepal%E2%80%99s%20engagement%20with%20TJ%20are%20now%20losing%20interest.%20This%20seems%20to%20have%20to%20do%20with%20%E2%80%98TJ%20fatigue%E2%80%99%2C%20a%20paucity%20of%20funding%2C%20as%20well%20as%20certain%20geopolitical%20considerations.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESome%20Western%20policymakers%20see%20Dahal%20as%20a%20pliable%20head%20of%20government%20of%20a%20strategically%20important%20Asian%20country%20that%20they%20must%20have%20%E2%80%98on%20their%20side%E2%80%99%20as%20China%20proceeds%20with%20a%20more%20aggressive%20continental%20policy%20of%20its%20own.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ENepal%E2%80%99s%20victims%20of%20conflict%2C%20in%20coordination%20with%20human%20rights%20defenders%2C%20have%20been%20fighting%20a%20lonely%20battle%20against%20a%20political%20class%20and%20polity%20that%20have%20been%20in%20thrall%20of%20the%20Maoists%E2%80%99%20momentum%20and%20their%20attempt%20to%20create%20a%20%E2%80%98new%20normal%E2%80%99%20in%20the%20polity%2C%20with%20a%20forced%20attempt%20to%20ensure%20past%20atrocities%20are%20forgotten.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhereas%2C%20the%20victims%20of%20conflict%20are%20united%20in%20not%20letting%20the%20perpetrators%20get%20the%20better%20of%20memory.%20The%20UN%20secretary-general%20has%20come%20up%20with%20a%20powerful%20position%20of%20support%20for%20a%20transitional%20justice%20process%20that%20is%20just%20and%20humane%2C%20and%20the%20victim%20representatives%20and%20rights%20defenders%20of%20Kathmandu%20are%20heartened.%20Their%20worst%20fears%20that%20bubbled%20to%20the%20surface%20when%20the%20secretary-general%E2%80%99s%20visit%20was%20hurriedly%20announced%20were%20not%20borne%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhat%20is%20required%20now%20is%20to%20keep%20watch%20for%20%E2%80%98spoilers%E2%80%99%20of%20the%20peace%20process%2C%20and%20they%20include%20many%20influential%20Nepalis%20who%20have%20over%20the%20past%20decade%20developed%20political%20and%20interpersonal%20relationships%20with%20the%20perpetrators%20of%20the%20conflict%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ELikewise%2C%20there%20is%20a%20Western%20diplomat%20(or%20two)%20who%20seems%20to%20have%20a%20low%20opinion%20of%20the%20Nepali%20yearnings%20for%20a%20just%20peace%2C%20rather%20than%20the%20peace%20of%20the%20cemetery.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EA%20group%20of%20civil%20society%20actors%20cautioned%20the%20secretary-general%20in%20a%20letter%20delivered%20as%20he%20departed%20Kathmandu%3A%20%E2%80%9CThere%20are%20national%20and%20international%20%E2%80%98spoilers%E2%80%99%20wanting%20to%20foist%20a%20perpetrator-friendly%20ending%20to%20the%20peace%20process%20in%20the%20name%20of%20elapsed%20time%20and%20geopolitical%20expediency.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewi