%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20plaintiffs%2C%20Tracey%20Silver-Charan%2C%20a%20flight%20attendant%20of%2037%20years%2C%20was%20awarded%20%24320%2C000%20in%20the%20verdict%20at%20the%20Alameda%20County%20Superior%20Court%20in%20California%2C%20per%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.washingtonpost.com%2Ftravel%2F2023%2F11%2F02%2Fflight-attendants-toxic-uniforms-verdict%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20Washington%20Post%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20newspaper%20reported%20that%20another%20woman%2C%20Brenda%20Sabbatino%2C%20received%20the%20biggest%20sum%20%E2%80%94%20%24750%2C000.%20She%20took%20early%20retirement%20after%20developing%20%26quot%3Bsevere%20chemical%20sensitivities%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20newspaper%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAttorneys%20told%20the%20AP%20that%20they%20represent%20more%20than%20400%20other%20AA%20flight%20attendants%20who%20are%20making%20the%20same%20claims.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESilver-Charan%20was%20part%20of%20a%20group%20of%20flight%20attendants%20who%20initially%20filed%20a%20lawsuit%20in%202017.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20The%20Post%2C%20which%20interviewed%20her%2C%20she%20first%20began%20to%20feel%20%26quot%3Bviolently%20sick%26quot%3B%20at%20work%20in%202016.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20was%20a%20few%20months%20after%20Twin%20Hill%20provided%20about%201.4%20million%20garments%20and%20accessories%20to%20more%20than%2065%2C000%20American%20Airlines%20employees%2C%20The%20Post%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESilver-Charan%20notified%20her%20supervisors%20of%20her%20issues%2C%20including%20rashes%2C%20respiratory%20distress%2C%20and%20feeling%20faint%2C%20according%20to%20The%20Post.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20mentioned%20that%20she%20would%20curiously%20feel%20better%20once%20she%20returned%20home%2C%20the%20newspaper%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20lawsuit%2C%20it%20was%20alleged%20that%20these%20problems%20were%20caused%20by%20formaldehyde%20applied%20to%20cotton%20blouses%20to%20decrease%20wrinkling.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cdc.gov%2Fniosh%2Ftopics%2Fformaldehyde%2Fdefault.html%23%3A~%3Atext%3DExposure%2520to%2520formaldehyde%2520can%2520irritate%2Cduration%252C%2520and%2520work%2520being%2520done.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAccording%20to%20the%20Centers%20for%20Disease%20Control%20and%20Prevention%2C%20%3C%2Fa%3Eformaldehyde%20can%20irritate%20the%20skin%2C%20throat%2C%20lungs%2C%20and%20eyes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESilver-Charan%20told%20The%20Post%20that%20she%20was%20the%20allowed%20to%20wear%20her%20old%20uniform%20but%20her%20health%20problems%20persisted.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20ultimately%20took%20six%20months%20of%20unpaid%20leave%20from%20work%2C%20according%20to%20The%20Post.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20her%20return%2C%20American%20Airlines%20said%20employees%20could%20buy%20uniforms%20from%20mass%20retailers%2C%20but%20she%20continued%20to%20experience%20health%20issues%20around%20coworkers%20who%20still%20wore%20the%20new%20uniforms%2C%20The%20Post%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20said%20her%20eyes%20looked%20as%20if%20she%20had%20been%20in%20a%20boxing%20match%20and%20that%20she%20was%20regularly%20getting%20bronchitis%20and%20laryngitis%2C%20The%20Post%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20a%20trial%20brief%20reviewed%20by%20The%20Post%2C%20American%20Airlines%20eventually%20terminated%20its%20contract%20with%20Twin%20Hill.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20airline%20did%20not%20immediately%20respond%20to%20Insider's%20request%20for%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feu.detroitnews.com%2Fstory%2Fbusiness%2F2017%2F04%2F14%2Fnew-uniforms-fly-american-crews%2F100489342%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20Detroit%20News%20reported%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20thousands%20of%20flight%20attendants%20reported%20adverse%20reactions%20to%20the%20uniforms%2C%20which%20included%20hives%2C%20rashes%2C%20migraines%2C%20respiratory%20issues%2C%20and%20thyroid%20problems.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20jury%20decided%20last%20week%20that%20the%2