0Hezbollah%20rockets%20but%20ended%20with%20exhausted%20troops%20withdrawing%20in%20some%20disarray%20and%20the%20IDF%20resorting%20to%20a%20massive%20air%20war%20that%20did%20huge%20damage%20to%20the%20infrastructure%20of%20much%20of%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThen%20there%20is%20Gaza.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBefore%20the%20current%20war%2C%20the%20IDF%20fought%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.aljazeera.com%2Fnews%2F2022%2F8%2F7%2Ftimeline-israels-attacks-on-gaza-since-2005%5C%22%3Efour%20other%20wars%20in%20Gaza%3C%2Fa%3E%20since%202007%2C%20primarily%20to%20control%20Hamas%E2%80%99s%20use%20of%20rockets%20and%20its%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fworld%2F2023%2Foct%2F28%2Fa-spiders-web-of-tunnels-inside-gazas-underground-network-being-targeted-by-israel%5C%22%3Egrowing%20network%20of%20infiltration%20tunnels%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20most%20significant%20one%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcasebook.icrc.org%2Fcase-study%2Fisraelpalestine-operation-protective-edge-gaza-13-june-26-august-2014%5C%22%3EOperation%20Protective%20Edge%20in%202014%3C%2Fa%3E%20which%20involved%20troops%20in%20a%20ground%20assault.%20In%20the%20event%2C%20they%20found%20the%20fighting%20extremely%20difficult%2C%20with%20the%20elite%20Golani%20Brigade%20experiencing%20serious%20casualties%20from%20the%20start.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOnce%20again%2C%20there%20was%20intense%20use%20of%20air%20power%20and%2C%20as%20in%20the%20other%20wars%2C%20it%20was%20civilians%20that%20suffered%20most.%20Overall%2C%20the%20Israelis%20lost%20more%20than%20300%20killed%20in%20those%20four%20wars%20but%20for%20the%20Palestinians%20in%20Gaza%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fcommentisfree%2F2023%2Foct%2F25%2Fisrael-hamas-war-assault-gaza-doomed-to-failure%5C%22%3Edeath%20toll%20exceeded%205%2C300%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EBitter%20experience%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EExperiences%20in%20other%20wars%20are%20relevant%20to%20what%20happens%20now%20in%20Gaza.%20After%20the%209%2F11%20attacks%20there%20was%20considerable%20international%20support%20for%20the%20US.%20War%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.opendemocracy.net%2Fen%2Fafghanistan_3849jsp%2F%5C%22%3Eagainst%20the%20Taliban%20seemed%3C%2Fa%3E%20inevitable%20though%20very%20few%20security%20analysts%20warned%20of%20the%20US-led%20coalition%20falling%20into%20a%20trap.%20The%20warnings%20were%20ignored%20and%2020%20years%20later%20the%20western%20troops%20finally%20retreated%20in%20disarray.%20Then%20came%20the%20Iraq%20war%20from%202003%2C%20with%20warnings%20once%20again%20ignored%20and%2C%20once%20again%2C%20with%20disastrous%20results.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAs%20to%20Gaza%2C%20there%20are%20multiple%20concerns%20about%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.opendemocracy.net%2Fen%2Fafghanistan_3849jsp%2F%5C%22%3Ewhat%20comes%20next%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20current%20incursions%20being%20far%20short%20of%20a%20full-scale%20ground%20intervention.%20There%20are%20sharp%20differences%20of%20belief%20of%20what%20should%20come%20next%20within%20the%20military%20and%20within%20Benjamin%20Netanyahu%E2%80%99s%20government%20as%20well%20as%20within%20Israel%20as%20a%20whole%2C%20with%20much%20of%20it%20heightened%20by%20the%20concern%20over%20the%20loss%20of%20international%20support.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20also%20concern%20about%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2023%2F10%2F24%2Fworld%2Fmiddleeast%2Fisrael-hamas-invasion.html%5C%22%3Eexperience%20of%20urban%20warfare%3C%2Fa%3E%20elsewhere.%20Just%20six%20years%20ago%2C%20it%20took%20nine%20months%20for%20the%20US-led%20coalition%20to%20take%20back%20the%20Iraqi%20city%20of%20Mosul%20from%20Islamic%20State.%20The%20US%20led%20the%20huge%20air%20assault%2C%20aided%20by%20France%2C%20the%20UK%20and%20other%20partners.%20The%20ground%20forces%20then%20were%20Iraqi%20troops%20and%20militias%20and%20they%20lost%208%2C200%20troops.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EA%20further%2010%2C000%20civilians%20were%20killed%2C%20and%20the%20old%20city%20was%20wrecked.%20It%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.iwm.org.uk%2Fhistory%2Fwhat-you-need-to-know-about-the-battle-of-stalingrad%5C%22%3Elikened%20to%20Stalingrad%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20early%201943.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EJust%20last%20year%2C%20a%20small%20force%20of%20Ukrainian%20soldiers%20held%20off%20a%20large%20Russian%20force%20for%20nearly%20three%20months%20in%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2022%2F07%2F24%2Fworld%2Feurope%2Fukraine-war-mariupol-azovstal.html%5C%22%3Esiege%20of%20the%20Azovstal%20steel%20works%20in%20Mariupol%3C%2Fa%3E%20using%20a%20network%20of%2024%20kilometres%20of%20Soviet-era%20tunnels.%20Hamas%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2023%2F10%2F28%2Fus%2Fpolitics%2Fgazas-tunnels-israel-ground-war.html%5C%22%3Ehas%20constructed%20vastly%20more%20tunnels%20under%20Gaza%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20is%20no%20doubt%20ready%20for%20months%20of%20combat.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThree%20weeks%20ago%2C%20Israel%20suffered%20a%20grievous%20loss%20and%20rightly%20got%20huge%20initial%20support%2C%20but%20that%20is%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fworld%2F2023%2Foct%2F29%2Fuae-calls-emergency-un-security-council-meeting-to-seek-pause-to-gaza-fighting%5C%22%3Ealready%20fading%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Worse%20still%2C%20there%20is%20a%20terrible%20inability%20of%20the%20current%20Israeli%20government%20to%20understand%20what%20it%20is%20dealing%20with%20in%20a%20ground%20invasion%20of%20Gaza.%20But%20the%20death%20toll%20tells%20us%20all%20we%20need%20to%20know.%20If%20we%20look%20at%20the%20five%20Gaza%20wars%20since%202007%2C%20including%20the%20current%20devastating%20war%2C%20the%20Israelis%20have%20lost%201%2C700%20people%2C%20but%20the%20Palestinians%20have%20lost%20more%20than%2013%2C000%20%E2%80%93%20and%20the%20numbers%20are%20rising%20by%20hundreds%20every%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EFor%20now%2C%20the%20public%20mood%20in%20Israel%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2023%2F10%2F29%2Fworld%2Feurope%2Fisrael-reservists-hamas-war.html%5C%22%3Estill%20supports%20the%20Netanyahu%20government%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20however%20unpopular%20it%20might%20have%20been%20just%20a%20month%20ago.%20But%20the%20small%20but%20persistent%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Fworld%2Fmiddle-east%2Ffamilies-israeli-hostages-taken-by-hamas-tour-europe-keep-focus-plight-2023-10-26%2F%5C%22%3Ecampaign%20by%20families%20of%20the%20hostages%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20them%20to%20be%20the%20priority%20is%20having%20an%20effect.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAbove%20all%2C%20it%20is%20the%20change%20of%20mood%20internationally%20that%20is%20a%20deep%20concern%20in%20Israel%20and%2C%20indeed%2C%20in%20the%20Biden%20administration.%20This%20was%20shown%20by%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fapnews.com%2Farticle%2Fun-resolution-vote-israel-hamas-gaza-truce-7eec00b0e28ef2036636b166b48ca030%5C%22%3Eweekend%20debate%20in%20the%20UN%20general%20assembly%3C%2Fa%3E%20when%20only%2012%20states%20supported%20the%20US%20and%20Israel%20in%20voting%20against%20a%20%E2%80%9Chumanitarian%20pause%E2%80%9D.%20Also%2C%20eight%20EU%20states%20were%20among%20the%20120%20supporting%20the%20motion%20and%20the%2045%20who%20abstained%20even%20included%20Britain.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20some%20previous%20Israeli%20military%20actions%2C%20the%20end%20has%20effectively%20come%20about%20when%20international%20support%20for%20Israel%20has%20collapsed%20or%20got%20close%20to%20that.%20If%20the%20ground%20war%20against%20Hamas%20had%20started%20within%20a%20few%20days%20of%20the%20shock%20of%20October%207%2C%20and%20if%20that%20operation%20had%20been%20successful%20and%20Hamas%20had%20collapsed%2C%20then%20Netanyahu%20could%20have%20claimed%20success.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThat%20has%20not%20happened%20and%20will%20not%20happen%20now.%20Instead%2C%20there%20is%20every%20prospect%20of%20a%20bitter%20war%20with%20many%20thousands%20m