define-vision-for-commonwealth-on-kenya-visit-and-its-being-hailed-a-success-12999333%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Fking-charles-had-chance-to-define-vision-for-commonwealth-on-kenya-visit-and-its-being-hailed-a-success-12999333%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22'Electoral%20Bond%20Scheme%20Contrary%20to%20PMLA%2C%20Favours%20Ruling%20Party'%3A%20Coalition%20Report%20Tells%20FATF%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F11%2F08223208%2Frupee-g9dbf1131e_1280.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3EMumbai%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Making%20a%20case%20for%20inclusion%20of%20the%20electoral%20bond%20scheme%20within%20the%20framework%20of%20the%20Financial%20Action%20Task%20Force%20(FATF)%2C%20the%20Global%20NPO%20Coalition%20on%20FATF%20in%20its%20recent%20report%20claimed%20that%20the%20nameless%20nature%20of%20the%20electoral%20bonds%20courts%20a%20significant%20risk%20of%20money%20laundering%20and%20corruption%2C%20along%20with%20a%20violation%20of%20citizens%E2%80%99%20constitutional%20right%20to%20know%20of%20favours%20to%20the%20ruling%20party.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20report%2C%20compiled%20by%20anonymous%20civil%20society%20actors%2C%20looks%20at%20the%20complex%20threat%20that%20the%20electoral%20bond%20scheme%20poses%20in%20a%20democracy.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20FATF%2C%20an%20intergovernmental%20organisation%20established%20in%201989%20by%20the%20Group%20of%20Seven%20(G-7)%20countries%2C%20leads%20a%20global%20action%20to%20tackle%20money%20laundering%2C%20terrorism%20and%20proliferation%20financing.%20Its%20Mutual%20Evaluation%20Review%20(MER)%20is%20scheduled%20today%2C%20November%203%2C%20to%20evaluate%20anti-money%20laundering%20laws%20and%20financing%20of%20terrorism%20in%20India.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%20The%20coalition%2C%20along%20with%20its%20other%20study%20on%20India%E2%80%99s%20attempt%20to%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fahead-of-fatf-meeting-report-says-india-weaponising-terror-financing-money-laundering-laws-against-ngos%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eweaponise%20terror%20laws%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20is%20pushing%20the%20intergovernmental%20organisation%20to%20look%20into%20the%20threats%20posed%20by%20the%20electoral%20bond%20scheme%20in%20the%20country.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20report%20and%20the%20FATF%20meet%20also%20comes%20at%20the%20time%20when%20the%20Supreme%20Court%2C%20after%20a%20three-day%20hearing%20starting%20October%2031%2C%20reserved%20its%20verdict%20in%20the%20batch%20of%20pleas%20challenging%20the%20legal%20validity%20of%20the%20electoral%20bonds%20scheme%20that%20allows%20anonymous%20donations%20to%20political%20parties.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9C%5BThe%5D%20electoral%20bond%20scheme%20is%20not%20merely%20opaque%20and%20non-transparent%20but%20opens%20a%20floodgate%20for%20money%20laundering%20through%20legal%20means%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20report%20argues.%20The%20anonymity%20that%20the%20scheme%20allows%20leads%20to%20%E2%80%9Cmysterious%20and%20indefinite%20donations%20which%20will%20be%20impossible%20to%20track%20down%E2%80%9D%2C%20the%20report%20says.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Global%20NPO%20Coalition%20only%20reiterates%20what%20the%20Reserve%20Bank%20of%20India%20has%20already%20flagged%20way%20back%20in%202017.%20In%20a%20letter%20addressed%20to%20the%20Union%20finance%20ministry%2C%20the%20RBI%20had%20objected%20to%20the%20introduction%20of%20a%20electoral%20bond%20scheme%20on%20the%20ground%20that%20it%20does%20not%20disclose%20the%20identity%20of%20the%20intervening%20persons%2Fentities%20buying%20the%20bonds%20and%2C%20therefore%2C%20the%20said%20scheme%20will%20affect%20the%20principles%20and%20spirit%20of%20the%20Prevention%20of%20Money%20Laundering%20Act%20(PMLA).%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EEmphasising%20the%20money%20laundering%20risk%2C%20the%20then%20Governor%20of%20the%20RBI%20wrote%20a%20letter%20stating%20%E2%80%9Celectoral%20bonds%20in%20physical%20form%20may%20exchange%20hands%20several%20times%20before%20reaching%20the%20political%20party%2C%20which%20would%20leave%20no%20trail%20of%20the%20transactions%20and%20in%20the%20process%20of%20providing%20anonymity%20to%20the%20contributor%20and%20to%20the%20political%20party%2C%20anonymity%20will%20be%20provided%20to%20several%20others%20in%20the%20chain%20of%20transfer%20of%20the%20electoral%20bonds.%20This%20can%20render%20the%20scheme%20open%20to%20abuse%20by%20unscrupulous%20elements%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESimilar%20concerns%20were%20raised%20by%20the%20Election%20Commission%20of%20India%20in%202018.%20In%20a%20separate%20letter%20addressed%20to%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Law%20and%20Justice%2C%20the%20ECI%20had%20stated%3A%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%20%E2%80%9CThis%20(electoral%20bond)%20opens%20up%20the%20possibility%20of%20shell%20companies%20being%20set%20up%20for%20the%20sole%20purpose%20of%20making%20donations%20to%20the%20political%20parties%2C%20with%20no%20other%20business%20of%20consequence%20having%20disbursable%20profits%E2%80%9D.%20The%20government%20not%20only%20overlooked%20these%20warnings%20but%20the%20minister%20of%20state%20for%20finance%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.huffpost.com%2Farchive%2Fin%2Fentry%2Felectoral-bonds-narendra-modi-election-commission-opposition-arun-jaitley_in_5dce3cd1e4b01f982eff5c62%3Fncid%3Dother_trending_qeesnbnu0l8%26utm_campaign%3Dtrending%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eallegedly%20lied%20on%20the%20floor%20of%20the%20parliament%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20that%20the%20ECI%20had%20not%20raised%20any%20concerns%20regarding%20the%20electoral%20bond.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Global%20NPO%20Coalition%20has%20found%20specific%20violations%20of%20the%20FATF%2C%20it%20says%20in%20the%20report.%20The%20%E2%80%98Recommendation%203%E2%80%99%20of%20the%20FATF%20requires%20countries%20to%20take%20effective%20measures%20to%20criminalise%20money%20laundering%20and%20give%20a%20wider%20meaning%20to%20the%20offence%20by%20including%20predicate%20offences.%20Recommendation%203%20also%20designates%20counterfeiting%20currency%20as%20a%20predicate%20offence%20for%20money%20laundering.%20The%20report%20states%20that%20the%20anonymity%20granted%20to%20the%20donor%20in%20the%20electoral%20bond%20scheme%20clearly%20violates%20the%20FATF%E2%80%99s%20recommendation.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFATF%2C%20in%20its%20report%20%E2%80%98Money%20Laundering%20and%20Terrorist%20Financing%20Related%20to%20Counterfeiting%20of%20Currency%E2%80%99%2C%20notes%20that%20counterfeiting%20is%20also%20a%20growing%20method%20of%20terrorist%20financing.%20Criminal%20groups%20have%20been%20active%20in%20using%20their%20covert%20network%20to%20introduce%20counterfeit%20currency%20into%20the%20financial%20system.%20The%20electoral%20bond%2C%20through%20its%20opaque%20design%20is%20prone%20to%20the%20risk%20of%20counterfeiting%20and%20channelling%20of%20illicit%20money%20in%20India%E2%80%99s%20financial%20system%2C%20the%20Global%20NPO%20Coalition%20claims.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Coalition%20has%20recommended%20a%20complete%20abrogation%20of%20the%20Electoral%20Bond%20Scheme%2C%202018%2C%20along%20with%20its%20suspension%20until%20the%20apex%20court%20passes%20its%20verdict.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ECorruption%2C%20although%20not%20explicitly%20covered%20by%20the%20FATF%2C%20time%20and%20again%20concerns%20have%20been%20raised%20and%20acknowledged%20by%20the%20intergovernmental%20organisation.%20The%20FATF%20also%20acknowledges%20the%20risk%20of%20money%20laundering%20through%20politically%20exposed%20persons%2C%20with%20the%20NPOs%20coalition%20points%20makes%20it%20binding%20on%20the%20government%20to%20make%20the%20identities%20of%20the%20funding%20identities%20(to%20the%20political%20parties)%20public.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20electoral%20bond%20scheme%2C%20the%20report%20finds%2C%20also%20curtails%20an%20individual%E2%80%99s%20constitutional%20right%20to%20know%20and%20in%20this%20case-%20right%20to%20know%20your%20candidate.%C2%A0%20A%20citizen%20can%20make%20an%20informed%20choice%20based%20on%20the%20full%20and%20complete%20information%20about%20their%20candidate%E2%80%99s%20credentials%20which%20includes%20their%20source%20of%20funds.%20But%20electoral%20bond%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20allow%20such%20disclosure.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EOther%20acts%20amended%2C%20ruling%20party%20%E2%80%99empowered%E2%80%99%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EEarlier%2C%20the%20Companies%20Act%2C%202013%20(%E2%80%98Companies%20Act%E2%80%99)%20and%20Representation%20of%20People%E2%80%99s%20Act%2C%201951%20(%E2%80%98RP%20Act%E2%80%99)%20mandated%20the%20political%20parties%20to%20reveal%20the%20details%20of%20their%20donations.%20But%20as%20the%20electoral%20bond%20scheme%20came%20into%20being%2C%20both%20the%20Companies%20Act%20and%20the%20Representation%20of%20People%E2%80%99s%20Act%20were%20amended%20making%20it%20%E2%80%9Ccompletely%20opaque%E2%80%9D%20and%20the%20information%20about%20the%20donor%20of%20the%20bonds%20and%20the%20source%20of%20their%20donations%20is%20not%20revealed.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20amendment%20virtually%20rendered%20the%20ECI%20powerless%2C%20as%20it%20no%20more%20has%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20power%20to%20seek%20information%20about%20donors%20of%20the%20bonds%20from%20political%20parties%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20Coalition%20finds%20in%20its%20study.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Coalition%20has%20also%20boldly%20inferred%20that%20the%20electoral%20bond%20scheme%20favours%20the%20ruling%20party.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20states%2C%20%E2%80%9CWhile%20no%20information%20regarding%20the%20electoral%20bonds%20is%20provided%20to%20the%20citizens%2C%20the%20said%20anonymity%20does%20not%20apply%20to%20the%20government%2C%20which%20can%20easily%20retrieve%20the%20donor%20details.%E2%80%9D%20The%20practice%2C%20the%20report%20says%2C%20is%20that%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20enforcement%20agencies%20is%20frequently%20misused%20by%20the%20ruling%20party%20to%20achieve%20political%20goals%E2%80%9D.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAdditionally%2C%20the%20banks%20are%20largely%20under%20the%20control%20of%20the%20Union%20finance%20ministry%2C%20therefore%2C%20the%20details%20of%20the%20donors%20can%20also%20be%20accessed%20by%20the%20ruling%20party.%20This%20%E2%80%9Cexclusive%20access%20to%20the%20donors%E2%80%99%20details%E2%80%9D%2C%20the%20Coalition%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9Callows%20the%20ruling%20party%20to%20track%20donations%20made%20to%20opposition%20political%20parties%20and%20arm-twist%20donors%2C%20and%20force%20them%20to%20make%20donations%20to%20the%20ruling%20party%20only%2C%20creating%20an%20uneven%20playing%20field%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAmong%20other%20issues%2C%20the%20electoral%20bond%20scheme%20also%20facilitates%20foreign%20funding%20within%20Indian%20electoral%20processes%2C%20which%20is%20not%20permissible%20under%20the%20law%2C%20the%20report%20has%20found.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESection%2029B%20of%20the%20Representation%20of%20the%20People%20Act%20prohibits%20political%20parties%20from%20accepting%20political%20donations%20from%20foreign%20sources.%20In%202014%2C%20the%20Delhi%20High%20Court%20found%20both%20the%20BJP%20and%20the%20Indian%20National%20Congress%20guilty%20of%20accepting%20donations%20from%20foreign%20sources%20in%20violation%20of%20Section%202%20(e)%20of%20the%20erstwhile%20Foreign%20Contribution%20(Regulation)%20Act%2C%201976.%20But%20interestingly%2C%20to%20bypass%20the%20said%20judgment%20and%20to%20further%20facilitate%20political%20donations%20from%20foreign%20sources%2C%20the%20electoral%20bond%20scheme%20promptly%20amended%20the%20provision%20relating%20to%20foreign%20donations%20under%20the%20Foreign%20Contribution%20(Regulation)%20Act%2C%202010%2C%20with%20retrospective%20effect%20i.e.%201976.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Coalition%2C%20in%20its%20report%20comments%2C%20%E2%80%9CIt%20is%20pertinent%20to%20note%20that%20the%20electoral%20bond%20scheme%20as%20it%20stands%20today%20facilitates%20foreign%20companies%20to%20make%20donations%20through%20their%20subsidiary%20companies%20in%20India%2C%20but%20in%20the%20absence%20of%20such%20an%20amendment%2C%20the%20judgment%20of%20the%20Delhi%20High%20Court%20would%20have%20been%20binding%2C%20and%20political%20parties%20would%20have%20faced%20punitive%20consequences.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAs%20a%20part%20of%20its%20recommendation%2C%20the%20Coalition%20has%20sought%20risk%20assessment%20of%20the%20electoral%20bond%20scheme%20and%20assessment%20of%20the%20threat%20of%20money%20laundering%2C%20terrorist%20financing%2C%20corruption%20and%20other%20threats%20of%20flow%20of%20illicit%20money%20through%20the%20scheme.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1699007988000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F11%2F08223208%2Frupee-g9dbf1131e_1280.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Felectoral-bonds-fatf-report-bjp-constitution%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20report%2C%20compiled%20by%20anonymous%20civil%20society%20actors%20calling%20themselves%20the%20Global%20NPO%20Coalition%20on%20FATF%2C%20looks%20at%20the%20complex%20threat%20that%20the%20electoral%20bond%20scheme%20poses%20in%20a%20democracy.%C2%A0%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A2%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Felectoral-bonds-fatf-report-bjp-constitution%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22