tions%20of%202%2C000%20employed%20adults%20in%20the%20UK.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EIt%20found%20that%2073%25%20of%20Gen%20Z%20are%20not%20afraid%20to%20take%20a%20pay%20cut%20to%20pursue%20a%20more%20fulfilling%20career.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EGen%20Z%20workers%20are%20known%20for%20their%20job-hopping%20tendencies%2C%20and%20a%20new%20survey%20has%20found%20that%20they%20expect%20to%20change%20their%20careers%20at%20least%20three%20times%20over%20their%20lifetimes.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERecruitment%20consultancy%20firm%20Resource%20Solutions%20recently%20surveyed%202%2C000%20adults%20in%20the%20UK%20between%20the%20ages%20of%2018%20and%2065%20who%20have%20been%20employed%20in%20the%20past%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20found%20that%20Gen%20Z%20plans%20to%20switch%20careers%20at%20least%20three%20times%20over%20their%20working%20life%2C%20which%20is%20once%20more%20than%20any%20other%20generation%20before%20them.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGen%20Z%20are%20more%20likely%20to%20prioritize%20their%20wellbeing%20and%20happiness%20than%20other%20generations.%20Around%2073%25%20of%20Gen%20Z%20said%20they're%20willing%20to%20take%20a%20big%20pay%20cut%20or%20step%20down%20to%20pursue%20a%20more%20fulfilling%20career%20path%2C%20per%20the%20survey.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%2024%25%20of%20Gen%20X%20and%2036%25%20of%20Baby%20Boomers%20were%20unwilling%20to%20ruin%20their%20career%20progression%20for%20the%20sake%20of%20better%20job%20satisfaction.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlmost%20two-thirds%20of%20Gen%20Z%20workers%20plan%20to%20leave%20their%20current%20employer%20within%20the%20next%20two%20years%20but%20almost%20half%20of%20Millennials%20and%20Boomers%20expect%20to%20stay%20for%20five%20years%20or%20longer.%20Nearly%20two-thirds%20of%20Gen%20X%20also%20expect%20to%20stay%20with%20their%20companies%20longer%20than%20five%20years.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhat%20a%20career%20meant%2010%2C%2020%2C%20or%2030%20years%20ago%20is%20no%20longer%20what%20it%20means%20to%20young%20professionals%20today%2C%26quot%3B%20Kristen%20Buckheit%2C%20managing%20director%20of%20EMEA%20at%20Resource%20Solutions%20said%20in%20the%20release.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOur%20data%20indicates%20an%20awareness%20from%20young%20professionals%20that%20more%20career%20changes%20may%20be%20necessary%20throughout%20their%20working%20life%2C%20which%20could%20be%20down%20to%20a%20myriad%20of%20elements%20impacting%20this%20generation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPeople%20are%20retiring%20later%20in%20life%2C%20the%20accelerated%20pace%20of%20technological%20advances%20%E2%80%94%20notably%20with%20AI%20%E2%80%94%20may%20render%20certain%20roles%20obsolete%2C%20and%20as%20the%20first%20to%20grow%20up%20with%20the%20internet%2C%20their%20acute%20awareness%20of%20how%20the%20world%20is%20changing%20is%20bound%20to%20impact%20how%20they%20feel%20about%20their%20future%20or%20purpose%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20survey%20of%2010%2C000%20Gen%20Zers%20in%20the%20US%20and%20UK%20by%20management%20consultancy%20firm%20Oliver%20Wyman%20earlier%20this%20year%20found%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-happy-job-hopping-quit-without-backup-oliver-wyman-2023-1%3Fr%3DUS%26IR%3DT%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3E70%25%20who%20said%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20they're%20%26quot%3Bloyal%26quot%3B%20to%20their%20companies%20are%20either%20actively%20or%20passively%20looking%20for%20a%20new%20job.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20may%20be%20that%20Gen%20Z%20doesn't%20share%20the%20same%20hang-ups%20about%20job-hopping%20as%20older%20generations%20because%20they%20think%20that%20being%20loyal%20to%20companies%20doesn't%20always%20pay%20off.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20study%20by%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgreat-resignation-reshuffle-job-switching-inflation-salary-raise-gas-employment-2022-9%3Fr%3DUS%26IR%3DT%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFederal%20Reserve%20Bank%20of%20Atlant