gainst%20the%20governor%2C%20requesting%20the%20top%20court%20to%20declare%20that%20Arif%20Mohammed%20Khan%20has%20failed%20to%20exercise%20his%20constitutional%20powers%20and%20duties%20by%20keeping%20Bills%20passed%20by%20the%20legislature%20on%20hold%20for%20an%20indefinite%20period.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EKerala%E2%80%99s%20move%20comes%20days%20after%20the%20DMK%20government%20in%20Tamil%20Nadu%20filed%20a%20petition%20in%20the%20apex%20court%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livelaw.in%2Ftop-stories%2Fgovernor-acting-as-a-political-rival-tamil-nadu-government-moves-supreme-court-against-governor-rn-ravis-inaction-in-assenting-bills-241228%5C%22%3Eaccusing%3C%2Fa%3E%20governor%20R.N.%20Ravi%20of%20positioning%20himself%20as%20a%20%E2%80%9Cpolitical%20rival%E2%80%9D%20who%20is%20%E2%80%9Cobstructing%20the%20State%20Legislative%20Assembly%E2%80%99s%20ability%20to%20carry%20out%20its%20duties%20by%20excessively%20delaying%20the%20consideration%20of%20bills%20that%20the%20Assembly%20has%20passed%E2%80%9D.%20The%20Punjab%20government%2C%20led%20by%20the%20Aam%20Aadmi%20Party%2C%20also%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Fcities%2Fchandigarh%2Fpunjab-government-supreme-court-governor-banwarilal-purohit-approval-2-bills-9008618%2F%5C%22%3Erecently%20moved%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20top%20court%20against%20governor%20Banwarilal%20Purohit.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fnews%2Fnational%2Fkerala%2Fkerala-government-moves-supreme-court-against-governor-arif-mohammed-khan-over-pending-bills%2Farticle67488446.ece%5C%22%3EAccording%20to%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Hindu%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20Kerala%20government%20raised%20the%20demand%20in%20a%20special%20leave%20petition%20on%20Thursday%2C%20November%202.%20The%20petition%20says%20the%20governor%20%E2%80%9Csubverted%20the%20Constitution%20and%20acted%20in%20a%20manifestly%20arbitrary%20manner%20by%20keeping%20the%20Bills%20passed%20by%20the%20State%20Legislature%20for%20an%20indefinite%20period%E2%80%9D.%20It%20sought%20a%20declaration%20from%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20that%20the%20governor%20is%20duty-bound%20to%20dispose%20of%20every%20Bill%20presented%20to%20him%20%E2%80%9Cwithin%20a%20reasonable%20time%E2%80%9D%20and%20a%20direction%20to%20Khan%20to%20do%20the%20same%20without%20any%20further%20delay.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20newspaper%2C%20three%20Bills%20passed%20by%20the%20legislature%20were%20pending%20with%20the%20governor%20for%20more%20than%20two%20years%20and%20three%20more%20for%20longer%20than%20a%20year.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20conduct%20of%20the%20Governor%20threatened%20to%20defeat%20and%20subvert%20the%20very%20fundamentals%20and%20basic%20foundations%20of%20the%20Constitution%2C%20including%20the%20rule%20of%20law%20and%20democratic%20good%20governance%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20petition%20argues.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Kerala%20government%20pointed%20out%20that%20the%20governor%20had%20cleared%20the%20Kerala%20Private%20Forest%20(Vesting%20and%20Assignment)%20Bill%2C%202023%2C%20which%20was%20presented%20to%20him%20on%20April%206%2C%202023%2C%20on%20September%2018.%20This%20shows%20that%20the%20non-disposal%20of%20the%20earlier%20Bills%20was%20a%20%E2%80%9Cconscious%20act%E2%80%9D%2C%20the%20petition%20says%2C%20according%20to%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Hindu%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CA%20Governor%20who%20acts%20in%20gross%20disregard%20and%20violation%20of%20the%20provisions%20of%20the%20Constitution%20cannot%20be%20said%20to%20be%20functioning%20in%20the%20discharge%20of%20his%20duties%20as%20a%20Governor%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20petition%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20past%20few%20years%2C%20opposition%20parties%20have%20repeatedly%20criticised%20governors%20appointed%20by%20the%20Narendra%20Modi%20government%2C%20accusing%20them%20of%C2%A0acting%20in%20violation%20of%20constitutional%20provisions%20and%20hindering%20governance.%20%E2%80%9CThey%20are%20wilfully%20undermining%20democratically%20elected%20state%20governments%20and%20choosing%20instead%20to%20obstruct%20governance%20as%20per%20their%20whims%20and%20fancies%2C%E2%80%9D%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Findia%2F8-political-parties-write-to-pm-modi-on-misuse-of-governors-post-and-central-agencies%2Farticleshow%2F98427401.cms%5C%22%3Eletter%3C%2Fa%3E%20signed%20by%20eight%20opposition%20parties%20and%20sent%20to%20Prime%20Minister%20Modi%20in%20March%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20constitution%20obliges%20governors%20to%20follow%20the%20%E2%80%9Cadvice%E2%80%9D%20of%20the%20cabinet%20led%20by%20the%20chief%20minister%2C%20the%20fact%20that%20there%20is%20not%20clarity%20about%20some%20key%20powers%20has%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Foffice-of-governor-threat-democracy%5C%22%3Eled%20to%20abuses%20of%20power%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20constitution%20is%20silent%20about%20three%20key%20areas%20regarding%20the%20governor%3A%20who%20to%20invite%20to%20form%20government%3B%20when%20to%20dissolve%20or%20call%20the%20state%20assembly%20into%20session%2C%20and%20when%20to%20approve%20Bills.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1699000199000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F03132819%2FF7m7Y5YaIAAeDNr.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fkerala-moves-sc-governor-arif-mohammad-khan-bills-hold-indefinitely%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Tamil%20Nadu%20and%20Punjab%20governments%2C%20also%20ruled%20by%20opposition%20parties%2C%20have%20also%20recently%20approached%20the%20top%20court%20against%20their%20respective%20governments.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A10%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fkerala-moves-sc-governor-arif-mohammad-khan-bills-hold-indefinitely%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Radhika%3A%20Was%20told%20I%20wasn't%20pretty%20for%20B'wood%22%2C%22content%22%3A%2